{"id":"gunflint-trail","generatedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z","designation":"National Scenic Byway","parkCode":null,"source":{"roadArticle":"County State-Aid Highway 12 (Cook County, Minnesota)","revisionId":1358886453,"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/County_State-Aid_Highway_12_(Cook_County%2C_Minnesota)"},"attribution":{"license":"CC BY-SA 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/","articleUrl":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/County_State-Aid_Highway_12_(Cook_County%2C_Minnesota)","text":"Route, junction, and history details adapted from the Wikipedia article \"County State-Aid Highway 12 (Cook County, Minnesota)\", by Wikipedia contributors, licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0."},"sources":[{"name":"Wikipedia","src":"wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/County_State-Aid_Highway_12_(Cook_County%2C_Minnesota)","revisionId":1358886453,"retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"},{"name":"Federal Highway Administration — National Scenic Byways","src":"fhwa","url":"https://www.fhwa.dot.gov/byways","retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"},{"name":"OpenStreetMap contributors (ODbL)","src":"osm","url":"https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright","retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"}],"endpoints":null,"itinerary":[{"place":"County State-Aid Highway 12 (start)","mileFromStart":0,"kind":"terminus","lat":48.1589,"lng":-90.89293,"seq":1,"src":"openstreetmap","control":[],"note":"The drive begins here","toNextMi":12.7},{"place":"High Cliffs Overlook","mileFromStart":12.7,"kind":"overlook","lat":48.0777,"lng":-90.74666,"seq":2,"src":"openstreetmap","control":[],"note":"","toNextMi":9.5},{"place":"Laurentian Divide","mileFromStart":22.2,"kind":"overlook","lat":48.06761,"lng":-90.54462,"seq":3,"src":"openstreetmap","control":[],"note":"","toNextMi":10.1},{"place":"Moose Viewing","mileFromStart":32.3,"kind":"overlook","lat":48.00201,"lng":-90.36174,"seq":4,"src":"openstreetmap","control":[],"note":"","toNextMi":20.1},{"place":"Scenic overlook","mileFromStart":52.4,"kind":"overlook","lat":47.77066,"lng":-90.31694,"seq":5,"src":"openstreetmap","control":[],"note":"","toNextMi":2.6},{"place":"County State-Aid Highway 12 (end)","mileFromStart":55,"kind":"terminus","lat":47.7546,"lng":-90.32444,"seq":6,"src":"openstreetmap","control":[],"note":"The drive ends here"}],"history":{"paragraphs":["The footpath was improved into a dirt road by Cook County in the 1890s to support the Paulson Mine. In the 1920s, local business owners paid for some improvements to the road; by 1957, it was paved from Grand Marais to Hungry Jack Lake. The last gravel section, south of Sea Gull Lake, was paved in 1979.","The road was designated a National Scenic Byway in 2009.","The Ham Lake Fire of spring 2007 severely impacted the Upper Gunflint Trail, burning over 40,000 acres (160 km2) in the Boundary Waters Canoe Area and Ontario's Quetico Provincial Park. The fire lasted several weeks and claimed almost 200 structures, although no one was seriously injured or killed. It was started accidentally by an unattended campfire at a campsite on Ham Lake. The fire drew national attention and a visit from Governor Tim Pawlenty, who inspected the damage first-hand. Despite the significant damage to the forest, most outfitters and commercial businesses have reopened and access to the region's lakes has resumed.","Located along a portion of the \"Old Gunflint Trail\", the post office was originally located in the Voyagers Inn and run by its first postmaster George Stapleton. It was later purchased by Lawrence F. Wooding (Gus) in the early 1950s and came to be known as \"Woody's Place\"."],"sourceSection":"History","src":"wikipedia"},"highlights":[],"references":[{"n":1,"text":"\"Cook County Logpoint Listings\". Minnesota Department of Transportation. 2010. Retrieved March 6, 2013.[permanent dead link]","url":"http://www.dot.state.mn.us/stateaid/trafficsafety/2010LogPointListings-byCounty082211/16_Cook_County_Log_Point_Listing_2010.xls"},{"n":2,"text":"Baran, Madeleine (October 19, 2009). \"Gunflint Trail, a 'road built for no reason' becomes National Scenic Byway\". MPR News. Minnesota Public Radio. Retrieved September 20, 2018.","url":"https://www.mprnews.org/story/2009/10/19/gunflint-trail-historic-designation"},{"n":3,"text":"1957 Official Road Map of Minnesota (Map). Cartography by The H.M. Gousha Company. Minnesota Department of Highways. Retrieved September 20, 2018.","url":"http://cdm16022.contentdm.oclc.org/cdm/compoundobject/collection/mdt/id/1189/rec/37"},{"n":4,"text":"1977-78 Official Highway Map - Minnesota (Map). Minnesota Department of Transportation. Retrieved September 20, 2018.","url":"http://cdm16022.contentdm.oclc.org/cdm/compoundobject/collection/mdt/id/1249/rec/57"},{"n":5,"text":"\"Gunflint Trail fire likely to expand\". startribune.com. Archived from the original on July 20, 2008. Retrieved October 27, 2007.","url":"https://web.archive.org/web/20080720073129/http://www.startribune.com/462/story/1170203.html"},{"n":6,"text":"Larry Wooding (June 15, 2021), A Chronology Of The Old Gunflint Trail Post Office, retrieved November 9, 2021","url":"https://archive.org/details/a-chronology-of-the-old-gunflint-trail-post-office"},{"n":7,"text":"Breining, Greg (February 28, 2008). \"A Glide Along Minnesota's Gunflint Trail\". The New York Times. Retrieved March 1, 2008.","url":"https://travel.nytimes.com/2008/02/29/travel/escapes/29gunflint.html"}],"routeLine":[[48.1589,-90.89293],[48.15886,-90.89197],[48.15797,-90.89138],[48.15763,-90.89058],[48.15669,-90.88999],[48.15613,-90.88949],[48.1563,-90.88844],[48.15675,-90.88743],[48.15708,-90.88636],[48.15739,-90.88532],[48.1579,-90.88452],[48.15825,-90.88368],[48.15872,-90.88315],[48.15939,-90.88324],[48.16002,-90.88323],[48.16045,-90.88252],[48.1606,-90.88163],[48.16114,-90.88105],[48.1617,-90.88067],[48.1622,-90.87998],[48.16302,-90.8792],[48.16382,-90.87881],[48.16413,-90.87771],[48.16418,-90.87586],[48.1639,-90.87509],[48.16368,-90.87386],[48.16357